annotation.TEXT: Alright, so where do I use the springboard? I have a feeling the answer to that will become blatantly obvious in a moment...
Aha! Midpoint! (If any of the other doors in that previous room led anywhere special, let me know.)
Ah, there's a vine! Well, that solves the mystery of how to reach that springboard. (The springboard would've gotten away with it too, if it wasn't for that meddling Goomstar.)
Whoops, gotta Start+Sel-- Whoa, hello!
Alright, let's go to The Mysterious Maze!
Yo, Goomstar, you're comin' with me.

There's probably a similar secret passage leading to the secret exit around here, but who knows where it could be... I can always search every nook and cranny the second time I play through this level, after I get the normal exit.
Hmm... There could be who knows what down there, but I'm going to take this upper route first.
Argh, that was kind of lousy...
...A single coin? ...Really? I risked my life for a single coin? ...Whatever. Let's move on.
Hello, and welcome back to Something else! Sorry it's been so long since the last Something else episode.
Okay, I can't kill the shark with a Goomstar. And, even worse, it crashed into the other Goomstar over there... Umm... I think I need to use the reset door again...
Oh, hey, it's another mermaid. You gonna help me across these munchers? Thanks!
Well, knowing how screen exits work, I should look for a door that's most likely not on the same screen as any other door.
There's some lag here, but I'm still too lazy to change that one ZSNES config setting.
Hey there, flying Wigglers. How's it going? Nobody's stomped you today, right? Good.
Okay, I found a good opening there.
Wait, there's nothing hidden above it? ...Whoa!

Hey there, Torpedo Ted. How's it going? Now, I'm assuming that this level is like most manga (going from right to left), because Torpedo Teds move slower when going to the left, so this is to help the player out.
Put a space in between "spin" and "jump", and capitalize "torpedo" and "ted".

However... Being glitch-killed doesn't sit well with me, so I'm going to go back in time a little bit here. (Of course, for a fair-and-square death, I wouldn't rewind, but that death certainly wasn't "fair-and-square".)
To be continued...
Yeah, no other Goomstars nearby. Maybe I could get one from further to the left, but it'll just be easier to use the reset door again.
R
Oh, please tell me I'm done dodging munchers for the rest of the level...
Nice, that Goomstar was in a good sprite slot to take out that Thwimp.
Oh, what? There are flying Wigglers here too? Okay, don't panic. As long as I don't stomp them, they won't go berserk on me.
Oh, it's a mermaid! Okay, cool. Took me a few seconds to be able to tell.
Crazy Night, eh? Alright, let's see just how crazy it is!
Maybe there'll be a maze coming up ahead.

Whoa, I did not see that shark coming that I barely dodged there!
Slow-motion instant replay time!
Ah, geez. Torpedo launchers on both sides of this double saw passage. This'll be tricky.
LOL, miss! I'm going to try again.
Umm... I think I'll go around and take a higher path.
Ah, so it's actually a Goomba. I shall call it... Goomstar!
Umm... Pretend there's a "The" before each instance of "Mysterious Maze" here. (I didn't feel like reshooting this part just to add the "The"s in there...)
Umm... I just missed getting into the opening up there, and that was a one-time use springboard. Well, I hope this door is a reset door.
Huh. I wonder why even use a door there if it was just gonna send me half a screen to the right on the same sub-level...
Whoa, careful. It's slippery. Also, the screen stops scrolling to the right here. Also, peach.
BGM: F-Zero GX - Big Blue
Oh, man. It's dark now, and this layer 3 fog is still obscuring my vision.

Hmm... But now that I think about it, in that one dark room where I took the upper path and entered the invisible door on top of a hidden coin block, I was probably meant to find the light switch on the lower path somewhere and have the spotlight reveal the hidden door for me, so I guess I kind of broke that puzzle. Oops, sorry.
The arrow points to the right, most likely at the pipe. However, is there something further to the left?
Heck, yeah!

Okay, there's a pencil, and... what is that? Starfy, perhaps? (I've been informed that it's actually a Starkiss from Mario & Luigi, but I'm going to call it by a different name for the rest of this episode.)

Umm... You know what? I think I'd rather use this Goomstar for a free embiggening. (Although, looking back, if I had managed to get at least 30 stars from bouncing off of it, I would've entered the bonus game, and gotten a free mushroom there.)
Well, now you guys get to see a number next to this "cute little skull" for the first time in my playthrough.
...Umm... I'm going for it!
Oh, I see a springboard up there, but I wonder how I reach it...
Okay, that worked.
Whoa, hello! I didn't even see that light switch before I hit it.
It's dark again. Whatever, I can see well enough.
Oh, man. It's almost like I've got a double-sized Ted here, but it's two Teds, of course. Also, I don't want to land on both of them at once, or the "ascending" glitch will likely damage me.
Whoa! Good thing for that peach I just grabbed!
There's a 1-up... Which I don't think I'll be going for.
There's 18 coins, a saw, a flying Wiggler that I'm not going to disturb, and a ? block.
Whoa, that's a lot of coins. I wonder how you reach them?
Oh, did I just find another secret passage? Well, I could be on my way to the secret exit after all, and that door up there might've just led to the normal exit.
Whoa, Podoboos! What're you guys doing here?
Oh, dude! It's a horde of mermaids! (I wonder if any of them have a hidden ability...)
Goal tape average so far: 1482 / 44 = 33.682 stars each.
ARGH!!! Oh, man... Will I have my first "fair-and-square" death here?
Goal tape average so far: 1522 / 45 = 33.822 stars each.
Going up!
Looks like it... Umm... That's a lot of doors... (Also, I guess that Podoboo chamber was not a vertical sub-level, since it's on the same sub-level as this place.)
Well, I didn't find anything. If there was something there that I missed, let me know.
Oh, good. A replacement peach.
I've gotta be careful not to let those Cloud Drops throw off my groove while I'm torpedo bouncing.
Whoa, what is that? Well, it's a sprite swap of a dolphin, obviously...
LOL at the saw.
Wait a minute, that pipe is blue, not green! Okay, let's assume all upside-down pipes of any color in this area are torpedo launchers.
There's something to the left here, I just know it. You don't just put in a spike-filled passageway with a Thwimp in it for no reason.
Huh? This place doesn't seem very maze-like...
I think it's safe to assume that all upside-down green pipes in this area are torpedo launchers.
Oh, geez! I just narrowly avoided stomping that flying Wiggler!
Oh, ho, ho! This game just pulled a Kirby-style puzzle on me, with a hidden door that's only visible in the spotlight!
Glitched demo count: 1 Space-time rewind count: 1
Oh, am I now in a vertical room?
What? This goalpost is blue-colored! This is only the normal exit? I thought for sure I was headed toward the secret exit with all those hidden paths I found.
There's another one of those star-shaped beings.

Huh. That unlocked the path to this Dedede Castle, which is named "DDDark Castle"! Gee, I wonder what that's going to be themed around... Anyway, someone voted for wherever The Mysterious Maze's normal exit leads, so let's do that!
Huh. Is this another reset door?
DELELELELELE WOOOOOOOP! (Or however you type out that sound effect.)
Well-timed jump FTW!
Hmm... There's a low tide here.
There's a floor down there! Now that I'm looking closely, I can barely see it! Could this lead to the secret exit? If so, that would be so awesome, especially since I found this totally by accident!
Okay, finally past that part that I should've gotten past about 1½ minutes ago. (Why was that springboard made to be one-time use anyway?)
I'm not sure why this one mermaid is here, unless there's something hidden to the right of that stack of barrels up there...
The ? block contains another peach. Hey, saw... Cut my butt to make this peach feel useful.
Whoa, it felt like I barely made that jump and barely dodged that Goomstar.
BGM: Kirby's Dream Land 3 - Sand Canyon 3
Aha! There's a (insert attempt to imitate HCBailly's voice here) secret passage!
Okay, no more fooling around. I know there's no time limit in this level, but I still don't want to be here forever.
Maybe this is the maze entrance?
Still can't fry sharks, but my fireballs can still be useful to inform me about things that are hidden by the fog.

Ooh, there's the goal! Aww... If I'd known the goal was right there, I'd've stuck with all those bunched-up Teds from earlier and gone for a big kill combo by hitting the goal with them all on screen.
Zwee!

Alright, I think I'm going to stop checking every pipe now. Also, two upside-down pipes there contain pumpkin plants (actually, "apple plants"), so I guess my previous assumption of all upside-down pipes being torpedo launchers was wrong.
Anyway, up next will be either Flower Island or The Mysterious Maze, but which one? Let's find out...
Oh, and don't worry. I didn't forget the BANANA PARTY vote!
There sure are a lot of spikes around here. Better swim carefully.
I'd say that this door on the far right seems like a good choice.
I don't like my positioning here. I'm going to back up for a second.
Place your votes for where you want me to go next, and that'll determine where I head next time!
Gah! Why was that one muncher at nearly the exact same height as the peak of the mermaids' jumps?
So, now I have three places that I can go to: Maximum Athletic 2, DDDark Castle, and Flower Island.
What kinds of tiles were behind the slope to allow me to get glitch-killed like that anyway?
Hmm... Maybe I should've sped up this part of the footage, but whatever. This won't take too long.
Umm... what? ...What the heck?! ...I don't think that was supposed to happen!

Well, let's dodge a few pencils in this small chamber here. (Maybe the door transition was used just to make sure there were no sharks nearby while I was dealing with these pencils or something like that.)
Close call there. Now, I wonder what's in that ? block... It might be something really good, but is it worth the risk?
I swear, it looked like I touched that muncher, but the game didn't declare me dead, so I'm not complaining!
Barely made that jump. Man, these jumps are getting to be really tight now...
Can't go back through that door.

Oh, and sorry, but I don't think I'll be doing a version of "What's on Yoshi's Menu?" with custom sprites. Also, sorry, but I completely forgot about trying to follow the "up, up, down" pattern during the next level.
Goal tape average so far: 1454 / 43 = 33.814 stars each.
That opens a path to that pipe up there, but I'm not going that way yet. Now to start my search for the secret exit, at ludicrous speed!
1-ups earned this time: 6.56. Bonus game average so far: 106.92 / 13 = 8.22462 1-ups each.
BGM: Kirby's Dream Land 3 - Ripple Field 1
Uh, oh. More Cloud Drops. However, since I stuck with this earlier Ted, which was launched from a lower altitude, I can totally Velveeta cheese this part!
Umm... No. I'm gonna let all those guys go off screen and let a brand new pair spawn.
Whoa! Just barely avoided that saw!
Oh, man. I'm getting close to The Evil Guy!

Ah, the red goalpost! So, this is the secret exit. Too bad I'm small, and I have to jump from the ground... Oh, but due to a bug that was fixed in this hack, things carried through pipes retain certain properties that would normally be forgotten in the original SMW, like the stun timer, so this Goomstar can wake up, letting me bounce off of it!
Can't go to the right, since the screen won't scroll any further that way.

I have a feeling that I'm gonna need this Ted eventually. Also, there's a peach that I don't need right now. Too bad I can't save it for later. Guess I'll take an intentional hit for hahas just to make it feel useful.
Also, it seems there's a layer 3 fog that's obscuring my vision here. Better pay close attention for things such as sharks.
Agh, stupid Cloud Drop! (I had to look up the name of that Yoshi's Island enemy.)
Okay, that jump was easier.
More mermaids, and more munchers to avoid. It seems like the munchers are getting trickier to avoid as I proceed.
Uh, yeah. Not even gonna try for that ? block. (If it holds something other than a single coin, let me know. UPDATE: Yep, it's just got a single coin. Totally not worth the risk.)
Whoa, found a hidden coin block.
Oh, geez. This is going to get really tricky...
Whoa! That guy nearly blindsided me! I think there should be traffic lights installed around here to reduce the risk of an accident involving flying Wigglers and Luigis.
And here are some more Goomstars for me to burninate.
For whatever reason, I thought to push up there in case there was a hidden door, and there was! Wow, talk about well-hidden!
Well, whatever that was, it's destroyable with a spin jump (so I can probably normal stomp it too).
Ah, it feels good to be embiggened.
Okay, dudes? Would you mind getting out of my way, please?
That unlocks Maximum Athletic 2: Electric Boogaloo. (Well, I don't know if it has anything electric or anything Boogaloo-related in it yet.)
BGM: Pokémon Diamond/Pearl/Platinum - Game Corner
Okay, there's a light switch, but... Nothing else? Is this just a dead end?
Okay, it was indeed a reset door. Alright, it should only take a moment to get the springboard again...
Yeah, I saw that door up there. Odds are it's a reset door. I'll come back to it if I need it.
Whoops, almost kicked that Goomstar through the slope there, but it got rejected.

Oh, but I have to be really careful with my peach, because doing a mid-air jump stops me from spinning. But, only the B button will trigger the mid-air jump, so I can press and release A all I want to adjust my bounce height without worry.
Yyyup!
Okay, maybe I didn't need that Ted from earlier, since there was another launcher there. However, I'm still going to stick with this first Ted.
I guess I'm not quite done with the level yet.
